        <updateDate>2005-05-17T14:36:29Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ Fair Taxes for Seniors Act of 2005 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to provide a one-time increase (from $250,000 to $500,000, or from $500,000 to $1 million for married taxpayers filing joint returns) in the exclusion of gain from the sale of a principal residence by a taxpayer who has attained the age of 50 before such sale. Provides that in the case of a joint return, only one spouse need satisfy the age requirement.]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
